          <m> (2,2) </m>. (Don't forget to make the direction a unit
          vector.) 
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          First I need to make the direction a unit vector. The length
          of the direction is <me>
            |v| = \sqrt{ 2^2 + 1^1 } = \sqrt{5} 
          </me>
          so the unit vector is <me>
            u = \frac{v}{|v|} = \left( \frac{2}{\sqrt{5}},
            \frac{1}{\sqrt{5}} \right) 
          </me>.
          Then I calculate the gradient of <m>f</m>, taking the
          partials in each variable. 
          <me>
            \nabla f = \left( -\sin (x - y), \sin (x - y) \right) 
          </me>
          Finally, the directional derivative is the dot product of
          gradient and the direction.
          <me>
            D_u f = \frac{1}{\sqrt{5}} (-2 \sin (x - y) + \sin (x- y))
            = \frac{-\sin (x - y)}{\sqrt{5}}
          </me>
          Finally I eavluate this at the point. 
          <me>
            D_u f (p) = \frac{-\sin (0)}{\sqrt{5}} = 0 
          </me>
        </p>
      </solution>
    </activity>
    <activity>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Calculate the directional derivative of <m>f(x,y) = xy - yz
          + yz^2 - x^3 </m> at the point <m> p = (3,1,-2) </m> in the
          direction <m>(1,3,1) </m>. 
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <p>
          First I need to make the direction a unit vector. The length
          of the direction is <me>
            |v| = \sqrt{1^2 + 3^2 + 1^2} = \sqrt{11} 
          </me>
          so the unit vector is <me>
            u = \frac{v}{|v|} = \left( \frac{1}{\sqrt{11}},
            \frac{3}{\sqrt{11}}, \frac{1}{\sqrt{11}} \right) 
          </me>.
          Then I calculate the gradient of <m>f</m>, taking the
          partials in each variable. 
          <me>
            \nabla f = \left(y - 3x^2, x - z + z^2, -y + 2yz \right) 
          </me>
          Finally, the directional derivative is the dot product of
          gradient and the direction.
          <me>
            D_u f = \frac{1}{\sqrt{11}} (y - 3x^2 + 3x - 3z + 3x^2 - y
            + 2yz) 
          </me>
          Finally I eavluate this at the point. 
          <me>
            D_u f (p) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{11}} (1 - 27 + 9 + 6 + 12 - 1 -
            4) = \frac{-4}{\sqrt{11}} 
          </me>
        </p>
      </solution>
