              \frac{-1}{t^2} \sin t + \frac{1}{t} \cos t \right) 
            </mrow>
            <mrow>
              \amp = GmM (\cos^2 t - t \sin t \cos t - \sin^2 t +
              t \sin t \cos t) = - GmM
            </mrow>
          </md>
          The potential energy has a constant rate of decrease. This
          path is a spiral in the <m>xy</m> plane with a reciprocal
          delay in radius, spiralling into the centre. It is
