          always increase. The fact that the potential energy
          increases linearly reflects that the potential energy is
          related to <m>1/t</m> but the radius is also decreasing as
          <m>1/t</m>: the alignment of these two means that the rate
          of increease of potential energy should be constant. 
        </p>
